    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Chickpeas, in one form or another, really are the ideal lunch item. Along with being inexpensive, healthiful, packed with protein, satisfying, quick to throw together, and easily transported, they are delicious eaten cold or at room temperature (this is important for those of us who refuse to use the communal office microwave). The chickpea-olive oil-lemon combination is always a winner. </></>I&#8217;m adding to the requests for Brandon&#8217;s soba noodle recipe. Pretty please?</p>
