      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/01/brown-bag-it/#comment-6831"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-12-12T22:34:00-05:00">Friday, December 12, 2014 at 10:34 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>As I stared at the uninspiring contents of my pantry, my gaze came to rest on a can of long forgotten chickpeas.  Damn, what was that yummy salad I used to make from a recipe on Orangette way back when.  A simple search and there it was, from 2007!  Thank you for the inspiration that still makes us happy 7 years later. Cheers.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-6831' data-commentid="6831" data-postid="1533" data-belowelement="comment-6831" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Back burner" aria-label='Reply to Back burner'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-66601" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Regine</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2007/01/brown-bag-it/#comment-66601"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2017-08-31T20:52:51-04:00">Thursday, August 31, 2017 at 8:52 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>So good. Thanks for the recipe. I once also added some crushed garlic, chopped chives, and  turmeric<br />
to brighten the colors.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-66601' data-commentid="66601" data-postid="1533" data-belowelement="comment-66601" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Regine" aria-label='Reply to Regine'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
    </ol>

      
  
